@jorisvandenbossche 

> I am in favor of putting this just in pandas.exceptions

why would you create *another* namespace ? when we already have a perfectly good one.

@wesm ``DatetimeTZDtype`` and other pandas extension types are not publicly exposed, API access is only via the ``pandas.api.types`` accessors (just for introspection ATM).

I don't think its time yet to write down a public for any dtype extensions types as the implementation is likely to change in pandas 2 and the only access (aside from the introspectors) is likely to be implementation writers (https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/375) and not libraries building on top of pandas.

the current API is privately exposed in ``pandas.types.dtypes``
